WEBVTT

00:16.320 --> 00:18.235
Sam, we're getting
straight gammas...

00:18.235 --> 00:20.324
...every half pulse at irregular
intervals.

00:21.760 --> 00:25.503
Let's move to right ascension 23
hours, 5 minutes.

00:25.503 --> 00:27.244
What the hell is going on out
here?

00:27.244 --> 00:29.246
Alpha Orionis is going
supernova.

00:29.246 --> 00:32.032
Sometime in the next 100 million
years.

00:32.032 --> 00:33.946
-Thursday.
-Excuse me?

00:33.946 --> 00:36.775
Thursday. It's going supernova
Thursday.

00:36.775 --> 00:39.778
If Alpha Orionis
were about to go supernova...

00:39.778 --> 00:42.216
...there would be silicon
flashes...

00:42.216 --> 00:43.782
...neutrino emissions....

00:43.782 --> 00:47.221
Even in daylight,
we would be able to see....

00:47.221 --> 00:48.396
You predicted this?

00:52.617 --> 00:54.141
Excuse me, Sam, I know you're
busy...

00:54.141 --> 00:55.533
...but it's almost noon.

00:55.533 --> 00:57.100
It's almost noon.

00:57.100 --> 00:58.797
It's noon, everybody. Let's go!

00:58.797 --> 01:00.103
Get in position! Let's go!

01:00.103 --> 01:01.539
What?

01:07.284 --> 01:08.764
What are you doing?

01:12.811 --> 01:14.639
You're pointing the damn thing
down!

01:16.163 --> 01:17.773
Professor,
there's this other phenomenon...

01:17.773 --> 01:21.037
...that Sam gives his priority
to at noon.

01:21.037 --> 01:22.386
Other priority? Now?

01:22.386 --> 01:24.475
Every day.

01:24.475 --> 01:26.825
What could be more important?

01:26.825 --> 01:30.264
Actually, this event isn't
strictly celestial.

02:23.795 --> 02:25.449
"I love you

02:25.449 --> 02:26.537
"He loved me

02:26.537 --> 02:28.365
"Said the little blue man

02:28.365 --> 02:31.107
"And scared me right out of my
wits"

02:39.550 --> 02:40.856
What is it?

02:43.989 --> 02:46.470
Remember I told you they were
going to pick a teacher...

02:46.470 --> 02:49.038
...to represent the district
at the school in New York?

02:49.038 --> 02:51.083
New York? You?

02:51.083 --> 02:52.737
That's great.

02:53.912 --> 02:56.219
Don't look at me like that.

02:56.219 --> 02:57.481
It's only two months.

02:57.481 --> 02:59.483
It's not like I'm going to the
moon.

02:59.483 --> 03:01.485
Two months is a long time.

03:01.485 --> 03:02.834
You could come.

03:02.834 --> 03:04.401
You know I can't.

03:04.401 --> 03:06.447
You could take off work.

03:06.447 --> 03:08.449
You just never
want to get out of this town...

03:08.449 --> 03:09.885
...and see the possibilities.

03:09.885 --> 03:12.409
Everything I want to see is
right here.

03:12.409 --> 03:14.411
You, the sky.

03:16.196 --> 03:19.721
I went to school
in that building right there.

03:19.721 --> 03:22.114
I hung upside down on this
jungle gym.

03:22.114 --> 03:24.943
In 20 years, I haven't moved an
inch.

03:24.943 --> 03:27.381
I fell in love with you
on this jungle gym.

03:30.949 --> 03:35.127
You know how much I want to do
this,
but I love you...

03:35.127 --> 03:38.261
...so if you tell me to stay,
I'll stay.

03:38.261 --> 03:39.219
Stay.

04:41.672 --> 04:44.284
Hey, Joe, hoist it up!

04:45.589 --> 04:46.895
It's got to be higher.

04:46.895 --> 04:48.592
Much higher.

04:48.592 --> 04:49.550
Higher.

05:19.406 --> 05:21.582
Mr. Green, what are you doing
here?

05:21.582 --> 05:23.497
I was just on my way to the
airport.

05:23.497 --> 05:24.672
Come here, Sam.

05:26.500 --> 05:27.892
Is Linda all right?

05:27.892 --> 05:29.372
Listen to me.

05:29.372 --> 05:32.375
Love can sometimes be
a very difficult thing.

05:32.375 --> 05:35.552
Listen up.

05:35.552 --> 05:37.119
"Dear Sam, this is the most
difficult thing
I've ever done.

05:37.119 --> 05:39.295
"I'm sorry I don't have the
courage...

05:39.295 --> 05:40.949
"...to do it face-to-face.

05:40.949 --> 05:43.343
"I never planned this, Sam."Mr. Green, what is this?

05:43.343 --> 05:46.041
She left you. I'm reading her
Dear John.

05:46.041 --> 05:50.306
"It's not you, Sam.
How can I make you understand?

05:50.306 --> 05:52.090
"Your life is set.

05:52.090 --> 05:55.137
"You have your stars
and your friends and the town,
but...

05:55.137 --> 05:57.357
