this crap?

23:59.960 --> 24:01.657
That was everything you had?

24:01.657 --> 24:04.443
What the hell is that for,
anyway?

24:05.618 --> 24:08.185
It's pretty, Sam.

24:20.850 --> 24:22.373
There we go.

24:25.768 --> 24:27.422
You can hear them?

24:29.163 --> 24:30.425
Are they talking?

24:32.949 --> 24:33.950
What about?

24:33.950 --> 24:35.604
You wouldn't be interested.

24:37.693 --> 24:39.042
Let me hear.

24:39.042 --> 24:40.304
It's wrong, Sam.

24:40.304 --> 24:41.697
Just for a second.

24:41.697 --> 24:44.439
I just want to hear her sweet
voice.

24:44.439 --> 24:45.614
Beg me.

24:45.614 --> 24:46.659
Please.

24:47.877 --> 24:49.618
Excuse me. Did you say
something?

24:49.618 --> 24:50.924
Please let me hear.

24:54.971 --> 24:56.059
Oh, my God.

24:56.059 --> 24:57.887
He's killing her.

24:57.887 --> 24:59.236
He's killing her, all right...

24:59.236 --> 25:01.151
...and she's loving every minute
of it.

25:01.151 --> 25:03.023
She's not like that.

25:03.023 --> 25:06.505
She likes to make love quiet
and slow and gentle.

25:06.505 --> 25:09.551
That girl of yours is a carnival
ride.

25:09.551 --> 25:11.379
This is horrible.

25:11.379 --> 25:13.250
This is worse than I'd imagined.

25:13.250 --> 25:14.338
Want me to turn it off?

25:14.338 --> 25:16.340
No. I need to hear it.

25:16.340 --> 25:18.168
How very brave.

25:27.308 --> 25:29.702
He's making love to her in
French.

25:29.702 --> 25:32.922
You know, Sam,
French men are very small.

25:32.922 --> 25:36.186
But not this guy.
It's like Godzilla's tail.

25:36.186 --> 25:38.232
He could take down Tokyo with
that thing.

25:38.232 --> 25:42.105
This has got to be
the longest orgasm I've heard.

25:42.105 --> 25:44.238
You want your charts?

25:44.238 --> 25:47.023
You enjoy making me suffer.

25:49.286 --> 25:50.592
Help me get him, Sam.

25:50.592 --> 25:52.463
Take the road less traveled.

25:52.463 --> 25:54.422
It'll make all the difference.

25:54.422 --> 25:56.293
Forget it.

25:56.293 --> 25:58.600
I will not get sucked into your
nightmare.

25:58.600 --> 26:00.907
Whatever.

26:00.907 --> 26:03.474
I think I can get this in
stereo.

26:07.609 --> 26:11.047
Welcome to New York, spy-boy.

26:34.941 --> 26:37.987
Slim Jim?

26:37.987 --> 26:40.686
Let's see what Ken and Barbie
are having tonight.

26:43.123 --> 26:44.385
Squab.

26:45.647 --> 26:48.171
He marinates it for half a day
in a lemon-wine sauce...

26:48.171 --> 26:49.912
...and he braises it with sugar.

26:49.912 --> 26:51.958
Please be quiet. I have to
concentrate.

26:51.958 --> 26:54.003
It's happening tonight.

26:54.003 --> 26:55.396
Smells delicious.

26:55.396 --> 26:57.311
I'll tell you a secret.

26:57.311 --> 26:58.747
It's not my recipe.

27:00.009 --> 27:03.534
I met an old man, and he said...

27:03.534 --> 27:06.537
...only prepare it for the woman
you love.

27:06.537 --> 27:08.975
Later I found out he made it
for a party he catered.

27:08.975 --> 27:11.586
Five hundred people.
He's just bursting with love.

27:11.586 --> 27:13.501
You should go to his restaurant
sometime.

27:13.501 --> 27:14.937
Good food, good people.

27:14.937 --> 27:18.637
Wait. Take the spoon like this.

27:18.637 --> 27:20.639
Just let her eat it, you maggot!

27:25.861 --> 27:28.516
It's the best thing I've ever
eaten.

27:28.516 --> 27:31.171
Will you shut up?

27:31.171 --> 27:32.955
I love to watch you eat.

27:34.740 --> 27:37.090
She hates having people watch
her eat.

27:37.090 --> 27:38.874
He's going down in flames.

27:38.874 --> 27:40.746
Here it comes.

27:40.746 --> 27:44.010
Oh, you know,
I heard the most amusing story.

27:44.010 --> 27:47.535
There is this...what are they
called?

27:47.535 --> 27:48.667
Sheep.

27:48.667 --> 27:50.538
Yeah. A breed of goats.

27:50.538 --> 27:52.975
And when they hear a sharp
sound,
they fall over.

27:52.975 --> 27:54.890
A sharp sound?

27:54.890 --> 27:56.326
Yeah. Anything.

27:56.326 --> 28:00.548
You clap your hands, and they
fall over.

28:00.548 --> 28:02.202
That's my story.

28:02.202 --> 28:04.117
They pass out
when they hear a sharp sound.

28:04.117 --> 28:05.771
It's true.

28:05.771 --> 28:08.512
They just fall over on the
ground.

28:08.512 --> 28:10.210
That's my kiss.

28:11.602 --> 28:12.995
That's my....

28:19.915 --> 28:21.700
Oh, not the food.

28:27.749 --> 28:29.838
I'll do it.

28:29.838 --> 28:31.274
I'll do whatever you want.

28:31.274 --> 28:32.885
This has to stop.

28:32.885 --> 28:35.061
I don't care about right or
wrong anymore.

28:35.061 --> 28:37.324
This must stop.

28:42.938 --> 28:45.114
All you gotta do is nudge him.

28:45.114 --> 28:47.029
Just graze him like that.

29:07.180 --> 29:08.224
Sorry.

29:12.315 --> 29:14.665
You're sorry?
You should be goddamned sorry.

29:14.665 --> 29:17.581
You think you can trample
a person and say you're sorry?

29:17.581 --> 29:19.366
Well, you can't.

29:19.366 --> 29:22.325
You can't trample on somebody's
life and say, "I'm sorry."

29:22.325 --> 29:24.763
There ought to be
something more you can say...

29:24.763 --> 29:27.504
...when you walk all over
somebody.

29:27.504 --> 29:29.637
And you're throwing food
everywhere!

29:43.042 --> 29:45.784
I think we took a detour
from the plan there.

29:45.784 --> 29:47.307
I really hit him, didn't I?

29:47.307 --> 29:49.483
You smacked him one, all right!

29:49.483 --> 29:50.440
How'd it feel?

29:50.440 --> 29:52.660
Great!

29:52.660 --> 29:55.489
What is your plan?
What do you want to do?

29:55.489 --> 29:57.926
I just want his dignity, that's
all.

29:57.926 --> 30:00.711
I want him penniless, hopeless,
loveless, finished off.

30:00.711 --> 30:03.018
I just wish him very, very ill.

30:03.802 --> 30:05.368
How ill are we talking here?

30:05.368 --> 30:07.544
I'm not saying I want him dead.

30:07.544 --> 30:09.851
But, should that occur,
people die all the time.

30:09.851 --> 30:11.679
Why should he be any different?

30:12.201 --> 30:13.724
Just thinking on my feet,
though.

30:13.724 --> 30:15.204
I don't have to decide
the death part right now.

30:15.204 --> 30:16.902
I can wait and see how I feel...

30:16.902 --> 30:19.208
...once his dignity's a thing of
the past.

30:19.208 --> 30:20.514
Am I boring you?

30:20.514 --> 30:22.124
Thank you, Anton.

30:24.779 --> 30:27.390
Maybe I shouldn't have hit him.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.479
He's just in love.

30:29.479 --> 30:32.700
He's just in love, the same as
me.

30:32.700 --> 30:34.223
Define love.

30:35.268 --> 30:37.009
Why?

30:37.009 --> 30:38.575
Because every other word
out of you mouth is "love."

30:38.575 --> 30:39.968
I'd like to know what it is...

30:39.968 --> 30:42.144
...this magical ideal of yours.
Define it.

30:42.144 --> 30:44.799
Well, it's like, I don't know.

30:44.799 --> 30:46.540
It's like all your life you walk
around...

30:46.540 --> 30:49.195
...with this feeling of
emptiness
in your stomach.

30:49.195 --> 30:51.110
You feel completely hollow.

30:51.110 --> 30:54.722
And when you're in love, you
feel...

30:54.722 --> 30:56.376
...not hollow.

31:00.771 --> 31:03.252
It's like without it, there's
nothing.

31:03.252 --> 31:06.081
A shell. A cavernous emptiness.

31:06.081 --> 31:08.344
Forget it. You can't define it.

31:09.606 --> 31:12.044
When I was a kid, my father had
this dog.

31:12.044 --> 31:14.785
It started to get weak and
sickly
so he took it to the vet.

31:14.785 --> 31:16.570
The doctor examines it and
says...

31:16.570 --> 31:18.833
...a maggot must've laid eggs
in the dog's butt.

31:18.833 --> 31:20.966
He says there's not much they
can do.

31:20.966 --> 31:24.404
The baby maggots have crawled up
and started to grow...

31:24.404 --> 31:28.321
...and eventually they're going
to eat
the dog alive from the inside
out.

31:28.321 --> 31:31.759
He says it should be put to
sleep
because it's an old dog, anyway.

31:31.759 --> 31:33.326
But Father won't do it.

31:33.326 --> 31:34.675
He takes it home.

31:34.675 --> 31:36.155
He puts it on the bed.

31:36.155 --> 31:38.026
He starts to reach up into the
dog...

31:38.026 --> 31:41.987
...picking out the maggots with
his fingers,
one by one.

31:41.987 --> 31:45.251
It takes him all night,
but he gets every last one.

31:46.817 --> 31:48.689
That dog outlived my father.

31:50.430 --> 31:51.953
That's love, Sam.

31:56.044 --> 31:58.960
You're not that tough, Maggie.

31:58.960 --> 32:01.180
I can tell you're not that
tough.

32:01.180 --> 32:04.270
And you can forget
about a career with Hallmark.

32:09.753 --> 32:11.320
Won't he miss the card?

32:11.320 --> 32:12.756
He won't know what hit him
till the bill comes...

32:12.756 --> 32:14.976
...'cause he only uses his
platinum.

32:20.242 --> 32:22.853
I'll just take everything in
this whole area.

32:24.855 --> 32:26.596
You know Anton's having an
affair?

32:26.596 --> 32:27.902
He is?

32:27.902 --> 32:29.860
That's what Linda's going to
think.

32:29.860 --> 32:30.731
Where are you sending them?

32:30.731 --> 32:32.298
To my Nana.

32:32.298 --> 32:34.169
The old battle-ax
should get a kick out of this.

32:35.040 --> 32:37.868
How much to put lipstick on the
monkey?

32:37.868 --> 32:40.001
Is that for you or for him?

32:40.001 --> 32:41.611
I don't touch the monkey.

32:41.611 --> 32:44.179
I don't want to have anything
to do with the monkey.

32:44.179 --> 32:45.746
How's 40?

32:45.746 --> 32:49.576
For 50 I'd strap on a garter
and wax her legs.

32:50.664 --> 32:52.057
Lovely lipstick, darling.

32:52.057 --> 32:53.754
Honey, you can't be treating me
this way.

32:53.754 --> 32:55.538
We've known each other too long.

32:55.538 --> 32:57.801
You can't even look me in the
eye.

32:57.801 --> 33:00.021
What? You're in love?

33:01.196 --> 33:04.069
You're in love with that man?

33:04.069 --> 33:06.680
That man could never make you
happy.

33:09.770 --> 33:12.468
What the hell is that? Shit!

33:12.468 --> 33:14.209
Good God! Kiss him, baby!

33:14.209 --> 33:16.516
Get this goddamned monkey off my
back!

33:25.046 --> 33:26.265
Give that man a hand!

33:26.265 --> 33:28.354
OK, that's fine.

33:28.354 --> 33:29.877
No problem.

33:32.010 --> 33:33.968
Greta thanks you. I thank you.

33:47.808 --> 33:49.766
Hello, sweetheart.

33:49.766 --> 33:51.551
Here we go. The target's home.

33:51.551 --> 33:53.553
You know bankers.

33:54.902 --> 33:56.556
They want to know every little
thing.

33:56.556 --> 33:58.775
What do they know
about the restaurant business?

33:58.775 --> 34:01.082
Are we packed?

34:01.082 --> 34:03.432
Hey, why don't we forget
about the Hamptons...

34:03.432 --> 34:05.260
...and spend the weekend in bed?

34:05.260 --> 34:06.522
There, that look!

34:06.522 --> 34:08.524
She sees it.

34:11.788 --> 34:13.355
Stay with her.

34:13.355 --> 34:16.010
Go back to her, Sam!

34:16.010 --> 34:17.011
Stick to her.

34:17.011 --> 34:18.795
Relax.

34:18.795 --> 34:20.406
Anything you wanted to tell me?

34:20.406 --> 34:22.234
What?

34:23.800 --> 34:25.802
What's that on your collar?

34:25.802 --> 34:28.675
Turn it up. I can't hear them.

34:28.675 --> 34:29.937
Oh, that.

34:31.112 --> 34:32.983
You'll never believe this.

34:32.983 --> 34:34.811
I'm walking through Washington
Square...

34:34.811 --> 34:36.030
...and there's this stupid man.

34:36.030 --> 34:37.336
You know, some guy with a
monkey.

34:37.336 --> 34:40.034
A street performer?

34:40.034 --> 34:41.557
That son of a bitch, yeah.

34:41.557 --> 34:43.429
The monkey jumps on me
and won't get off my back.

34:43.429 --> 34:45.648
You're kidding.

34:45.648 --> 34:49.087
The people all around, they are
laughing.

34:49.087 --> 34:51.350
And the monkey is kissing me,
kissing me.

34:51.350 --> 34:54.222
I think it peed on me. It
stinks.

34:54.222 --> 34:56.659
What is she laughing at?

34:56.659 --> 34:58.618
I don't know.

34:58.618 --> 35:01.273
What do you think of the story?
I'll show you what I think.

35:01.273 --> 35:02.796
I'll get you.

35:15.722 --> 35:18.072
Let's forget about the Hamptons.

35:18.072 --> 35:21.031
It's going very well, don't you
think?

35:21.031 --> 35:23.643
Drink up, buddy,
'cause tonight we're going in.

35:25.035 --> 35:26.602
There they go.

35:26.602 --> 35:29.170
We want to go to the Long Island
railroad.

35:31.477 --> 35:34.001
Idiot never even changed the
lock.

35:38.571 --> 35:40.094
Close it.

35:46.492 --> 35:48.146
It's so much smaller than it
looks on TV.

36:16.826 --> 36:18.480
In the couch.What?

36:18.480 --> 36:20.395
In the couch. Don't make it
obvious.

36:20.395 --> 36:22.528
-You're kidding.
-Just do it.

36:22.528 --> 36:24.486
Why were you wearing them?

36:24.486 --> 36:26.793
Authenticity.

36:48.684 --> 36:49.903
What are you going to do?

36:49.903 --> 36:51.600
Receipts.

36:51.600 --> 36:53.080
Why are we whispering?

36:53.080 --> 36:54.386
I don't know.

37:22.936 --> 37:24.198
Mine.

37:56.143 --> 37:57.275
Mine.

38:06.980 --> 38:08.547
Mine.

38:10.113 --> 38:11.114
Mine.

38:13.291 --> 38:14.727
Perfection, yes?

38:17.033 --> 38:18.034
[WE] Voilà.[WE]

38:23.779 --> 38:25.303
This is comfortable.

38:31.221 --> 38:33.398
This is what you wear to walk
about...

38:33.398 --> 38:35.356
...with everything swinging
freely.

38:39.795 --> 38:42.015
Look at me. I am so fabulous.

38:42.015 --> 38:43.712
I am so beautiful.

38:43.712 --> 38:45.714
Witness my matted chest hairs.

38:45.714 --> 38:47.237
They are nice, no?

38:56.812 --> 38:58.466
What do you think?

39:02.427 --> 39:04.211
You look....

39:27.713 --> 39:29.192
Look at this.

40:42.483 --> 40:45.181
I love you, Linda.

40:45.181 --> 40:47.096
I hate you, Anton.

40:54.234 --> 40:56.410
I got to make the bed.

41:01.371 --> 41:03.461
Sure. Right.

41:20.216 --> 41:21.522
Can you clean the kitchen?

41:21.522 --> 41:23.306
We should get out of here.

41:24.612 --> 41:26.658
I think we should talk.

41:27.136 --> 41:29.704
Nothing to talk about.

41:29.704 --> 41:32.533
Yes, there is. Something
happened.
I would like to talk about it.

41:32.533 --> 41:34.317
Nothing happened, Sam.

41:34.317 --> 41:36.494
OK? Nothing happened.

41:36.494 --> 41:38.234
I know what you're going
through.

41:38.234 --> 41:39.671
I'm going through the same
thing.

41:39.671 --> 41:41.847
Get this straight, pal. I'm not
like you.

41:41.847 --> 41:43.892
I don't care what you're going
through.

41:43.892 --> 41:46.112
If I thought you and I were
alike
in the most trivial way...

41:46.112 --> 41:48.114
...I would tie a rope around my
neck.

42:22.409 --> 42:23.628
I'm sorry.

42:43.473 --> 42:45.606
Last night wasn't us, Maggie.

42:45.606 --> 42:48.566
I know. I'm glad you know.

42:48.566 --> 42:51.873
Maybe we should just,
I don't know, call it a day.

42:58.880 --> 43:02.928
You know what's going to happen
to her,
Sam?

43:02.928 --> 43:06.845
He's going to make her feel
like she's the only woman in the
world.

43:06.845 --> 43:09.238
When he looks at her,
it'll be just like a kid...

43:09.238 --> 43:13.068
...looks at a Christmas tree
all lit up and shiny.

43:13.199 --> 43:18.073
For the first time,
she'll feel like she's really
been seen...

43:18.073 --> 43:20.380
...and really loved.

43:20.380 --> 43:21.773
And then...

43:24.210 --> 43:28.040
...and then three weeks later...

43:28.040 --> 43:30.042
...she'll find a pair of panties
in the couch.

43:30.042 --> 43:32.566
Then she'll learn that she was
just a steppingstone.

43:32.566 --> 43:35.351
That he was just using her to
get a visa.

43:42.358 --> 43:44.012
It'll change her, Sam.

43:52.194 --> 43:54.240
I understand.

43:55.371 --> 43:57.635
You know what's always bothered
me?

43:59.027 --> 44:02.204
I can't see the side of her
face.

44:02.204 --> 44:05.120
I can never see the left side of
her face...

44:05.120 --> 44:07.340
...when she's standing here
in the kitchen...

44:07.340 --> 44:09.603
...because of these things in
the window.

44:09.603 --> 44:11.649
So help me move this over a
little bit.

44:16.175 --> 44:17.219
Good?

44:17.219 --> 44:18.525
A little more.

44:20.745 --> 44:21.702
Good.

44:38.023 --> 44:40.199
What?

44:40.199 --> 44:43.855
I saw the sign about the job.

44:43.855 --> 44:45.552
I don't want a half salt shaker
on the table.

44:45.552 --> 44:47.293
You go and refill it
immediately.

44:47.293 --> 44:49.077
Pardon.

44:49.077 --> 44:51.427
Il faut tout leur apprendre!

44:51.427 --> 44:53.516
Nothing here for you. Go.

44:53.516 --> 44:54.692
Why?

44:59.566 --> 45:01.873
Do I need a reason in my own
restaurant?

45:01.873 --> 45:03.352
Of course not.

45:03.352 --> 45:04.440
I don't like your face, that's
why.

45:04.440 --> 45:05.703
Just go.

45:19.934 --> 45:21.240
Wait.

45:22.589 --> 45:24.460
Why did you do that?

45:24.460 --> 45:26.549
Why did I do what?

45:26.549 --> 45:28.813
The flowers.
Why did you move it like that?

45:28.813 --> 45:31.032
I wanted them to be
in the middle of the table.

45:31.032 --> 45:32.860
Why?

45:32.860 --> 45:34.296
Because it was...

45:34.296 --> 45:36.821
...it was just something that I
had to do.

45:38.300 --> 45:41.129
Perhaps at heart you seek
perfection, no?

45:41.129 --> 45:42.957
Yes, perhaps I do.

46:01.454 --> 46:03.064
Almost done?

46:06.459 --> 46:08.591
Almost.

46:08.591 --> 46:10.593
Good work.

46:12.160 --> 46:14.946
Why don't you stop for a moment?

46:22.170 --> 46:24.651
I know who you are.

46:24.651 --> 46:28.655
It took me a little while, but I
figure it out.

46:33.094 --> 46:35.009
Dry off your hands.

46:39.535 --> 46:41.320
It was you who attacked me that
day.

46:41.320 --> 46:43.888
Couldn't see your eyes,
but I don't forget a face.

46:43.888 --> 46:47.369
You didn't put an address down
on your application.

46:47.369 --> 46:50.329
You are homeless, aren't you?

46:50.329 --> 46:51.678
That's OK. Don't be ashamed.

46:51.678 --> 46:53.071
You know, I was hungry myself
once.

46:53.071 --> 46:55.334
I would see a rich man, a man I
envied...

46:55.334 --> 46:57.858
...I would want to strangle him.

46:57.858 --> 46:59.729
But that's not the way I found.

46:59.729 --> 47:01.514
You must better yourself.

47:01.514 --> 47:02.863
Don't be ashamed.

47:02.863 --> 47:05.518
Give me your hand. Come on.

47:06.867 --> 47:09.957
I like a man who fights for what
he wants.

47:09.957 --> 47:12.351
But if you ever mess with me
again...

47:12.351 --> 47:15.833
...I'll rip out your eyes and
rape your skull.

47:15.833 --> 47:17.747
Excuse my French.

47:17.747 --> 47:20.011
Was a good punch, huh?

47:20.011 --> 47:21.621
Solid.

47:21.621 --> 47:23.666
It was nice.

47:23.666 --> 47:26.278
So you did all his dishes
and got punched in the face.

47:26.278 --> 47:27.670
What was your thinking there?

47:27.670 --> 47:30.935
I'm missing something.
What was your plan?

47:30.935 --> 47:33.720
No plan. I just wanted to face
him.

47:33.720 --> 47:35.983
I wanted to be
in the same room with him...

47:35.983 --> 47:37.419
...to talk to him.

47:37.419 --> 47:40.205
In my mind, he was like a god.

47:40.205 --> 47:42.033
Now what do you think?

47:42.033 --> 47:44.774
Well, it's not like he's God God
anymore.

47:44.774 --> 47:48.778
He's more like a volcano god or
a sea god.

47:48.778 --> 47:51.346
One of those sub-gods.

47:51.346 --> 47:53.522
Maggie, I think he likes me.

47:56.351 --> 47:59.050
One thing, though.

47:59.050 --> 48:02.314
He said something
about having sex with my skull.

48:02.314 --> 48:03.532
He says that to everybody.

48:03.532 --> 48:05.230
Don't worry about it.

48:07.406 --> 48:09.016
Sorry.

48:09.016 --> 48:11.976
I don't like the sound of it.

48:11.976 --> 48:13.978
I don't like the image that it
conjures.

48:13.978 --> 48:16.371
I can't honestly say I blame
you, Sam.

48:21.986 --> 48:24.162
So I let go with my hands...

48:24.162 --> 48:26.991
...and I fell off the top
of the jungle gym face-first...

48:26.991 --> 48:29.471
...and I broke this tooth in
half.

48:29.471 --> 48:32.431
I'm laying on my back,
blood all over my face...

48:32.431 --> 48:34.955
...the kids are yelling,
the teachers are freaking out...

48:34.955 --> 48:37.131
...and I look up, and there she
is.

48:37.349 --> 48:38.959
She's just looking down at me...

48:38.959 --> 48:41.440
...with this worried little
smile on her face.

48:41.440 --> 48:45.487
I swear to God, when I saw her,
the pain just went away.

48:45.487 --> 48:47.794
Once I took pictures
of a bunch of ducklings...

48:47.794 --> 48:49.578
...who imprinted on a gardener.

48:49.578 --> 48:51.537
They thought he was Mama...

48:51.537 --> 48:53.060
...and they used to chase him
around
all day...

48:53.060 --> 48:56.498
...while he drove around
on his lawn mower.

48:56.498 --> 48:57.760
That's exactly what it feels
like.

48:57.760 --> 48:59.937
It's like she's branded on my
brain.

48:59.937 --> 49:01.590
What happened to this guy...

49:01.590 --> 49:04.245
...is that one day he forgot
the ducks were there.

49:04.245 --> 49:07.379
He put the mower in reverse,
chewed them to pieces.

49:08.597 --> 49:10.948
Don't you know any happy
stories?

49:12.471 --> 49:14.038
There he is.

49:18.129 --> 49:20.044
That's him!

49:20.044 --> 49:21.393
Let's get him!

49:29.401 --> 49:30.837
Our work is done.

49:39.672 --> 49:41.891
Midgets coming out of the blue.

49:41.891 --> 49:44.459
I had to protect myself with one
of them.

49:44.459 --> 49:46.070
Midgets coming out of the blue?

49:46.070 --> 49:49.334
Yeah.
Little children shooting perfume
at me.

49:50.378 --> 49:51.814
From their guns.

49:51.814 --> 49:53.729
Perfume from their guns?

49:53.729 --> 49:55.644
Yeah. Water guns?

49:55.644 --> 49:56.776
Squirt guns?

49:56.776 --> 49:58.560
Yeah, I think. Squirt guns.

49:58.560 --> 50:00.040
Spooky, huh?

50:00.040 --> 50:02.521
Wait, the loaf, I think it's
burning.

50:02.521 --> 50:05.045
Look at him trying
to weasel his way out of it.

50:05.045 --> 50:06.655
He didn't do anything, Sam.

50:06.655 --> 50:09.571
Anton, don't you think it's a
little peculiar...

50:09.571 --> 50:12.531
...that little children would be
shooting
perfume at you?

50:12.531 --> 50:15.403
I thought it was something
American kids do.

50:15.403 --> 50:17.492
A fad, I don't know.
We should have some salad.

50:17.492 --> 50:20.582
It's very expensive perfume,
Anton.

50:20.582 --> 50:22.323
I used to wear that perfume.

50:22.323 --> 50:24.717
Good call, Sam!

50:27.198 --> 50:30.027
Last week you had lipstick on
your collar.

50:31.332 --> 50:32.768
From the monkey.

50:34.770 --> 50:37.382
And now perfume...

50:37.382 --> 50:40.167
...from squirt guns
from rich New York kids.

50:40.167 --> 50:41.821
What are the odds...

50:41.821 --> 50:43.475
...of something like that
happening to one person?

50:43.475 --> 50:45.303
I don't know. Ask a
mathematician.

50:45.303 --> 50:47.261
Ask your old boyfriend,
the Milky Way man.

